page.title: 15SHAPWICK NATURE RESERVE (1)
page.content: To enter the Nature Reserve you have to apply to the{Nature Conservancy {Council}for a special permit. The Nature Reserve is an area of rough woodland - with a stream running through it. If you are careful and quiet and if you look very carefully there are a lot of animals, insects and plants which you can see. { INSECTS/BUGS. PLANTS/FLOWERS. ------------ -------------- Water boatman. Poppies. Dragonflies. Buttercups. Six-spotted Ladybird.Daisies. Caterpillars. Dogrose. Centipede. Ragged Robin. Spiders. Thistle. Mayfly. Cowspray. Butterflies-Cabbage Orchid. White. Oak Apple. Moth.
